How can I use PHP to find the longest word in a given list that can be typed using only the right side of a standard QWERTY keyboard layout? Here's a PHP code that uses an array to store the list of words and checks if all characters in a word are present in the right side of the keyboard:
```php
$words = array("pearl", "queue", "earthquake", "keyboard", "treaty", "teapot", "murmur", "yurt");
$rightSide = array('y', 'u', 'i', 'o', 'p', 'h', 'j', 'k', 'l', 'n', 'm');
$longest_word = "";
foreach ($words as $word) {
    $is_right_side = TRUE;
    for ($i = 0; $i < strlen($word); $i++) {
        if (!in_array(strtolower($word[$i]), $rightSide)) {
            $is_right_side = FALSE;
            break;
        }
    }
    if ($is_right_side && strlen($word) > strlen($longest_word)) {
        $longest_word = $word;
    }
}
echo "The longest English word that can be typed using only the right side of the keyboard is: " . $longest_word;
```
How can I modify this code to also display the length of the longest word?

To modify the PHP code to display the length of the longest word that can be typed using only the right side of a standard QWERTY keyboard layout, you can simply store the length of the longest word along with the word itself. After finding the longest word, you can then echo both the word and its length. Here's how you can modify the code:

```php
$words = array("pearl", "queue", "earthquake", "keyboard", "treaty", "teapot", "murmur", "yurt");
$rightSide = array('y', 'u', 'i', 'o', 'p', 'h', 'j', 'k', 'l', 'n', 'm');
$longest_word = "";
$longest_length = 0;

foreach ($words as $word) {
    $is_right_side = TRUE;
    for ($i = 0; $i < strlen($word); $i++) {
        if (!in_array(strtolower($word[$i]), $rightSide)) {
            $is_right_side = FALSE;
            break;
        }
    }
    if ($is_right_side && strlen($word) > $longest_length) {
        $longest_word = $word;
        $longest_length = strlen($word);
    }
}

echo "The longest English word that can be typed using only the right side of the keyboard is: " . $longest_word;
echo "\nIts length is: " . $longest_length;
```

In this updated version of the code, a new variable `$longest_length` is introduced to keep track of the length of the longest word. After updating the longest word, the code also updates the `$longest_length` with the new word's length. Finally, it prints both the longest word and its length.
